SubString.CExoString: The smell of woodsmoke draws you closer to the dancing fire. The sap of a birch log burns blue at its center.
The corpse of your enemy, burning slowly.
The corpse of your enemy, burning slowly.
Loosely nailed, this wooden crate appears intended for temporary storage
A carefully constructed marker denoting a point of interest.
Ogres Lair ! We Smash you good !

Day 1:
These monsters are afraid of humans and will only go out if you stay close close to the ship for a short while - Captain Anders
Day 3:
I have noticed different kind of monsters living on the island like kobolds, bugbears, goblins, ogres, strange giant beetles as well as many animals - Captain Anders
Day 6:
It seems the kobolds and the goblins are always at war for the cliff, right now I'd say the goblins got the upper hand...they seem to be much stronger than kobolds, but then there are more kobolds. The bugbears on the other hand tend to prefer their cave to warmongering. The Ogres are strange...they seem to capture anything they find and use it for religous sacrifices - Captain Anders
Place this object in any area where you want tracking to occur. Set Will to the DC of tracking in this area.
